<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Defile" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Defile,</orth> vb. 1) to make unclean, to render dirty: <cit><quote>they that touch pitch will be --d,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 60</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>pitch that --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.3" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 3</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.456" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 456</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.196" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 196</bibl>. Quibbling: <cit><quote>--s the pitchy night,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 4, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in a pitched field; ay, --d land,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 1.2.231" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 2, 231</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>houses are --d for want of use,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 1.4.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 4, 37</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to pollute, to sully: <bibl n="shak. luc 787" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 787</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 787" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 787</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 787" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 787</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.4.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 4, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.410" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 410</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.301" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 301</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 3, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 3, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.131" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 131</bibl>.
<lb />Absolutely: <cit><quote>vows were ever brokers to --ing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 173" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 173</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>